alert.note: Alert for Franklin; Jefferson; Leon; Liberty; Wakulla (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued January 25 at 10:11AM EST until January 25 at 11:15AM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Wakulla County in Big Bend of Florida... Southeastern Liberty County in Big Bend of Florida... Southwestern Jefferson County in Big Bend of Florida... Southeastern Leon County in Big Bend of Florida... Franklin County in Big Bend of Florida... * Until 1115 AM EST. * At 1011 AM EST, severe thunderstorms were located along a line extending from near Crawfordville to 17 miles southwest of St George Island, moving east at 20 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... Carrabelle, St. Marks, Eastpoint, Apalachicola, Woodville, Crawfordville, St George Island, Wakulla, Franklin, Sopchoppy, Cody, Shadeville, Leon Sinks, Royal Bluff, Wakulla Springs, St George Island St Pk, Eight Mile Pond, Panacea, Medart and Bethel. TORNADO...POSSIBLE HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...<.75 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM EST for Big Bend of Florida. For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building. A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM EST for Big Bend of Florida.
